    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a species of very large, heavy, long-legged, short-necked ruminants with large distinctive palmate antlers; they inhabit the northern parts of North America and Eurasia. They are called "elk" in Europe, but the term "elk" refers to another animal, Cervus canadensis, in North America.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
